metadata.name: Unfolded #296
metadata.description:
A plane is repeatedly folded over itself, choosing creases either at random, or according to some pattern (like a grid). These creases form the boundaries of the individual textured tiles.

Once the folds are complete, they are undone in reverse order, recreating the original plane. With each unfolding, the orientation of each crease (as a mountain or a valley), and each tile (facing up or down) is recorded as a sequence of 1s and 0s. Tiles are colored and textured according to similarities in these binary sequences, giving rise to subtle symmetries and repetitions.

Written in vanilla JS & HTML5 Canvas.

metadata.name: Floral Fusion #97
metadata.description:
This collaboration takes Nomadic Frame’s original photos and uses Steve’s Makerspace’s code in p5.js to turn the photos into flow fields.

Nomadic Frame: "Floral Fusion" is an exciting collaboration between Steve's Makerspace and myself. By combining my flower macro photography with Steve's use of fxParams technology, we have produced unique and beautiful generative art.  We are thrilled to share this artwork with you, and hope it brings joy and inspiration.

Steve: This is my first collaboration, and my great challenge was how to add something interesting with code that would not take away from Nomadic Frame’s amazing nature photography, but would somehow enhance it.  I hope I’ve done it justice. 

You might want to start by locking everything from Zoom down, and then play with all of those after you update the other params.  For the original photo color (almost), put “tint color” to white, “hue shift” to zero, and “color variance” to five.  For “shape definition,” a lower amount means more defined.  Horizontal and vertical focus applies when zoom is greater than 1.  Vertical focus goes from top to bottom.  “Add grain” option uses Dave Pagurek’s grain shader.

After opening, hit 2-5 for higher pixel density and “s” to save a png.  Resizing the window reverts to pixel density 1.

This token is part of the SESSIONS SERIES co-curated by the NFT Museum of Newberry, SC and Fort Gallery NFT.

metadata.name: FSM #91
metadata.description:
FSM is a visual grid-system based on autopoiesis, the principle of self-organization through self-reproduction central to cybernetics. At the heart of FSM is a computational mechanism, a finite-state machine (FSM), which generates sequences of visual outputs by activating particular agents and cycling them through varying sets of configurations.

The grid-system in FSM is segmented along three axes: horizontal, vertical, and diagonal. This segmentation constitutes the machine’s parametric space.

Certain agents and configurations are programmed to appear exclusively in specific grid segments, illustrating a principle of spatial distribution.

Similarly, spatial distribution is mirrored by temporal distribution. Specific agents and configurations are set to emerge at predetermined time intervals. This interplay turns FSM in a self-organizing system living on the blockchain.

The underlying grid of the animation is responsive. Try to change your window size to get different aspect ratios and grid configurations. On the project page you'll find a tool to adjust some parameters via queries components.
Please visit: http://fsm.julian-h.de for more information

CONTROLS
[f] To enter fullscreen mode
[spacebar] Play or pause the animation
[s] Export current frame as a PNG
[g] Capture a small GIF
[G] Press once to start capturing a GIF and press [G] again to stop the capture process.

Created using p5.js and GLSL.

Julian Hespenheide, 2023

metadata.name: Just, Steven! #280
metadata.description:
Just,Steven - is a shell that has always followed me, or has been a part of me, I never fully understood. This is a character who ironically, because of the many social culture shifts in his life, began to resort to the way of putting other people's faces and stories on himself. At first it was necessary to adapt in a certain circle of society so as not to be a black sheep, after a few years he stopped noticing how the consciousness itself uses the stories or phrases he has already heard from absolutely different people received during a conversation, news or other, another of the features is the numerous personalities of Steven.

I am creating this project because I have long wanted to try to tell people that being yourself is the most difficult and wonderful feeling. My goal is to get an animated movie adaptation on Netflix, the script will be written by anyone who wants to participate in the community. 

Peace be with you all!

metadata.name: Mei(梅) #36
metadata.description:
Mei(梅):

"Mei" is an oriental art piece featuring the imagery of plum blossom, a symbol of courage and perseverance in traditional Chinese culture.

The generative system at the backend of "Mei" is an exploration of this cultural symbol by modern art language. The basic elements of the paintings are merely circles and enclosed flow field shapes. A great variety of short and light strokes of such elements are used across the paintings. Xuan paper is occasionally used as background, which is a painting material since the Tang dynasty.

Mei's outputs span different stages of plum blossom from winter to spring. The scene also changes from a calm day to snowy or even stormy weather. The consistent yet complex senses and feelings reflected are surprisingly versatile.

metadata.name: Lonely Tree #164
metadata.description:
The bridges have been burned, wrapped in loneliness, and covered in the ashes caused by your fire.

The sound of the wind whispers, longing to carry you away.

With a shattered face, you see others in the distance, they are close, but so far away; the emptiness of this edge is closer than any of them.

But, is it? Looking within isn't hard, it's just a glance and knowing, but it's painfully hard to see.

Disjointed, you tell yourself over and over again that it wasn't for lack of effort.

But, is it? Looking within isn't hard, it's just a glance and knowing, but it's painfully hard to see.

Perhaps you weren't so lonely, perhaps you're not lonely after all.

=== 

CAUTION 

Please be aware that this artwork demands a certain level of CPU power due to the substantial number of elements that need to be rendered on the canvas. Depending on your hardware and the specific features obtained, the rendering process may take anywhere from a few seconds to several minutes to complete.

metadata.name: Flowingcles #108
metadata.description:
"Flowingcles" is a generative art piece that showcases a mesmerizing collection of  circles and abstract shapes. This unique collection invites art enthusiasts to embark on an inspiring visual journey.

Some pieces feature abstract shapes accompanied by a noise effect, reflecting restlessness and energy, while others present a more serene atmosphere with minimalized noise effects. These two approaches offer collectors the freedom to choose the one that resonates with them the most.

The "Flowingcles" collection consists of a total of 128 original pieces. Each artwork has been generated with a unique combination, ensuring individuality and distinctiveness. By incorporating these pieces into their collections, art enthusiasts can adorn their homes, offices, or galleries with a sense of unparalleled art experience and authenticity.

"Flowingcles" stands as a prominent example of modern art, showcasing dynamism, aesthetics, and originality. This collection pushes the boundaries of art and takes viewers on a captivating visual journey. Therefore, me invite art lovers to explore the "Flowingcles" collection and become a part of this visual spectacle:)

metadata.name: Pixel Plus #48
metadata.description:
I took inspiration from retro video games and pixel art in this style but added a modern twist by incorporating intricate details and designs.
I separated and carefully arranged the pixels to form intricate patterns, shapes, and images. And I gave the effect a distinctly retro feel by using limited colors and blocky pixels to create creativity and imagination.
The result is a visually striking piece that captures the viewer's attention with bold colors, sharp edges, and meticulous attention to detail. Each pixel is carefully placed to create depth and texture, resulting in a nostalgic and contemporary work of art.
Made by p5.js
